name: Charm Chump; Puck Luck; Compulsion; Admission Impossible

description: Blood is spilled on the snowy floor of the Mouse Territories as the battle between Celanawe, Lieam, and the one-eyed owl rages on. Tired, frozen, and with little hope of getting medicine to Lockhaven, their only goal now is survival. Deep beneath the surface in the abandoned Darkheather, Saxon rejoins his companions Sadie and Kenzie as they may have discovered a way home. The winter mission that lead the Guard's finest away from Lockhaven is nearing an end, and one that they will not all live to see.

This is it: the exciting conclusion to the face-off between Captain Marvel and Black Adam! With Black Adam back to full power and four of the seven Evils still at his side, Billy and Mary need to team up to figure a way to defeat him. All this, plus a trip to the Rock of Eternity!

volume.name: Billy Batson and the Magic of SHAZAM!

description:
Leaping from Stan Lee's hit Sci Fi Channel TV series Who Wants to be a Superhero? onto the comics page -- it's the Defuser in "Future Imperfect!"

When traditional police methods fail to stem the ever-growing tide of crime in his home city, Detective Jarrett Crippen takes matters into his own hands.

Devising an astonishing array of nonlethal weapons and a high-tech battle armor that boosts his performance to 110% of human capacity, Jarrett storms the streets as the Defuser! The criminals won't know what hit them!

volume.name: Who Wants To Be A Superhero?: Defuser

description: While called # 86, this was really Lady Luck # 1, they just dropped all the other features that had been in Smash Comics, gave it all over to Lady Luck and changed the title.
name: Lady Luck

description: DarkMinds: Macropolis #1 will begin the third volume of the popular sci-fi thriller series. In this series we join Nagawa and Nakiko as they desperately try to track down a brutal serial killer unlike any other they've ever encountered. This killer's twisted plan is to include Nagawa in on his horrific rampage. Before each murder, the killer sends Nagawa information on how to stop the murder before it happens. With each demented challenge, Nagawa races against time to try and save the innocent citizen whose life hangs in the balance. And with each murder the stakes grow higher and higher. Will Nagawa make it on time or will another victim die? What is the killer's motivation? And why, of all people, has he targeted Nagawa for this sick game? DarkMinds: Macropolis will carry its readers on a dark, winding path of murder and intrigue mixed with tender human emotion. It's packed with the non-stop action and the dark, nourish, crime-thriller roots established so richly in the original DarkMinds series by Pat Lee and Adrian Tsang.
name: Welcome To Macropolis

description: Welcome to the shadowy world of DarkMinds, the chilling story of a prolific serial killer and two special investigators charged with bringing the killer to justice. Set in the not-so-distant future city of Marcropolis, DarkMinds is a synthesis of classic detective fiction and the broader genre of sci-fi cyberpunk. This Issue: Join us for: A brutal killer on the loose, a headless body with a heartbeat and a six-foot-five security guard named "Tiny" as the mad journey through Macropolis continues! The race is on to apprehend the city's newest and most sadistic killer in this, the second installment of the eight-issue serial. Agents Nagawa and Nakiko are desperate for leads but the meticulous killer has covered his tracks well. Tired, frustrated and angry our heroes appear beaten. That is until the daring killer pays them an in-person visit, delivering a "gift" that intensifies the chase to new heights. How long can the killer avoid Nagawa and Nakiko? How many will suffer in the process? And how long until Nagawa and Nakiko become targets themselves?

The chase to stop Macropolis' newest and most savage killer continues. In this issue, the killer lures Nagawa to the most dangerous area of the city; challenging him to try and stop another brutal murder before it happens. Will he get there on time? Just wait until you see what stands in his way! Also, Nakiko's mysterious collapse is explained... and explanation you have to read to believe!

Nagawa... a killer? Nakiko... a kidnapper? Can it be true? Join us for the fourth installment of the action-packed murder mystery to find out! Nagawa continues his hunt for Macropolis' most brutal serial killer. Nakiko continues her quest to find Nagawa despite her "condition." How soon before it all comes crashing together? And how many innocents will suffer in the process? Darkminds: Macropolis #4 continues the twisting tale of murder, action and mystery!

After barely escaping Jun's trap with their skins, Nagawa, Mai and Reiko try to make sense of the chaos around them. Thinking that they had evaded the worst of their troubles, they are gravely mistaken as a city of cyborgs and robots seem to awaken from every corner of Macropolis from some unknown slumber. Converging from all directions, a common purpose seems to drive them all - a hunger for one Reiko Tetsunori. Meanwhile, events transpire that may soon cause a reunion between Nagawa and a certain ex-partner.
name: The Hunger

description: Questions are answered and mysteries are unraveled in this climatic issue. What has been driving the cyborgs of Macropolis to mimic the murders of Paradox? Why do they now seek the Neon Dragon's, Reiko Tetsunori? Why have dreams and voices of his long-dead partner haunted Nagawa? All will be answered with the return of a familiar face - Nakiko.
name: Born Again

description: Darkminds Volume II follows the tales of intrigue and deception that seem to follow Nagawa and Mai wherever they go. Originally sent to investigate a number of serial murders, they now find themselves in the thick of a conspiracy that may place the fate of the planet in jeopardy. In this issue, Nakiko, the Special Investigations Unit cyborg-agent thought to be dead over a year ago, is reunited with her old partner, Nagawa. However, the pair won't have a chance to catch up on old times as she tells of what was revealed to her during her "slumber", exposing the person who has been the true threat underlying everything... Vargas. But time is running out as Vargas' plans for a twisted world revolution are about to come to fruition. Can Nagawa, Mai and Nakiko hope to stop him? This issue sets the stage for the conclusion of Darkminds Volume 2 in next month's final issue.
name: A Million And One

description: The tale of Nagawa and Mai reaches its conclusion in the final issue of Darkminds Volume 2. Once simply a pair of SIU agents on the trail of a serial killer, a bizarre sequence of events leaves the two entangled in a far-reaching conspiracy which could cost them their lives. Reunited with the resurrected cyborg, Nakiko, they now stand before an enemy that they cannot hope to overcome. Is this their end, or has Vargas gravely underestimated his opponents?
name: Final Bow

description:
1. The Good Samaritan (Newsboy Legion and Guardian)

2. The Numismatist's Noose (Star Spangled Kid)

3. The Parrot Who Wouldn't Talk (Penniless Palmer)

4. The Battle of the Big Swamp (Liberty Belle / written by Don Cameron)

5. In a Fog (Super Sleuth McFooey / by Jack Farr)

6. Dr. Gaunt, Genius (Robotman)
name: The Good Samaritan

description: Desperation takes hold in the rebellion. While Sam struggles to forge a fragile alliance with the Martian colony forces, a dark figure resurfaces, creating a staggering loss for the Militia. As war hurtles toward its final battle, can Sam conquer the conflicts of her past to protect humanitys future?

1. Cover by David Ross and Mike Gustovich.
  2. "No Title" written by Roy and Dann Thomas, penciled by David Ross, inked by Mike Gustovich, colored by Carl Gafford and lettered by David Cody Weiss.
  3. One page pinup of the JSA by Michael Bair.
  4. "An Epilegomena to 'The Last Days of the Justice Society"" written by Roy Thomas two page text piece on the inside front and back covers.
  5. One page printing of the unreleased story "The Impossible Crimes".
  6. Back cover is a reprint of the cover to All-Star Comics #12.

Notes:

  • Most characters have cameo appearances.
  • Lois Lane of Earth-2 cameo flashback appearance.
  • Teen Titans, the Outsiders and the Freedom Fighters have cameo appearances.
name: The Last Days of the Justice Society

volume.name: Last Days of the Justice Society Special

name: Edgar Rice Burroughs Tarzan : The Crown of Opar

description:
1) Beep Beep The Road Runner - The Turn of the Tide - 6 pages - feat. Taz

2) Beep Beep The Road Runner - Loaded For Riches - 6 pages - feat. Elmer Fudd

3) Beep Beep The Road Runner - Bad Bargain - 5 pages

4) Beep Beep The Road Runner - The Meal Steal - 5 pages - feat. Porky pig, Cicero Pig

Copyright 1979, by Warner Bros. Inc.
name: The Turn of the Tide

description: First issue! When a force of alien invaders threatens the world, the elite armored squadron known as the Armorines may be the Earth's only hope! But why do these aliens seem so familiar?
name: Return To Sender

description: Spider Aliens, Spider Aliens and more Spider Aliens! Gunny and crew continue their mission into bug country as death, betrayal, and a new member make their way into the ranks of the Armorines!
name: Burnin' Love

description: An Armorine dies in this issue! Not a hoax! Not a lie! Not a cheap marketing gimmick! This comic book based on Acclaim's Armorines: Project Swarm video game continues in full stride as the armored heroes travel into the desert and begin to unravel the mystery behind their insectoid adversaries.
name: Return To Sender

description:
New York City is a jungle, a dangerous landscape of bad guys and worse guys.

Terry Smalls is a self-serving community activist who makes his living off of his famous black militant father, Wayne Smalls. When he accepts a gift from Antanku, a strange African cleric, he finds himself at the center of a bloody, violent power struggle, and becomes heir to a timeless African tribal legend.
name: The Legend of the Black Lion

description: Artist. Brother. Sorcerer. Manipulator. Savior. Just who is Master Darque? With a thirst for knowledge and power, Darque will take any means necessary to ensure his reign. One poor soul with nothing to lose learns this first hand, as he becomes a pawn in the Master's game.
name: Master Darque

description: Solicitation: Picking up where the Master Darque event story left off, this four-issue limited series jet-sets Alexandre, his prot g Brixton, and sister Sandria across the occult underworld to the gothic spires of New York City. And once we get there, we learn that there are villains far less honorable than the tattooed one!
name: The Musik Of The Hours

description: Darque plays power games with the twins: the prize a soul so twisted it could fuel the Armageddon!
name: Warship

description: Sandria, Brixton and the mysterious Rose help Darque stay one step ahead of the deadly Epoch Twins. But when the fabric of time itself begins to fray, how long can Darque hold back the shadows?
name: The Road To Shadow

description: Sandria is in deadly peril; the barriers between worlds are crumbling; and an army of demons are waiting to enforce the Epoch Twins' claim to rule. Even the power Darque has consumed for centuries may not be enough to hold back the tides of Hell -- unless... There's a secret player Darque needs on his side -- before it's too late!
name: The End Is Beginning

description: Our lifetime is determined solely on a singular event. What becomes of one's existence after death? Explore the mysteries of the world beyond, the Deadside, where the end for some is only just the beginning.

Faith can carry one through the most perilous of journeys. It is that hope and belief that the end result will all be worth it. But when you've entered the Deadside, and your journey is now bound to eternity, how long can you hold on to faith, when the end is never in sight?

After death you enter the Deadside same as countless others, a drop in an ocean of endless despair. Yet even the Deadside has a hierarchy, a way of things, games to be played. Some see this as an opportunity. Yet how can you win when you are bound to the realm of the damned?

Doctor Tomorrow goes in an entirely new direction to deal with a new generation. Using his new contacts, he seeks out the daughter he never knew. But she's not what he was expecting and he expects that she'll hate him! Journey into the Space Age as the Race for Tomorrow continues...
name: Yesterday's Grace... Tomorrow's Child

description: When one of the immortal Sons of Mog is hideously murdered in a Hollywood back alley Gilad and Aram will need to recruit the help of a young man named Archer to find the killer. But what will they do when all evidence points to their own brother, Ivar the Timewalker, as the culprit?
name: Time

description: Betrayals and bizarre alliances abound as Aram joins forces with Archer to stop the Warmaster from destroying the world in his effort to neutralize a mysterious cosmic entity.
name: Archer & Armstrong

description: Here it is, the final showdown between the Forever Family and their archnemesis, Blackworks! Donald Kelvin has set his sights on Ivar's map of Everwhen, a fold map capable of traversing time itself. His catspaw- Shalla Redburn! When Redburn makes a daring attempt to steal the map, the Timewalker decides he's had enough. Gilad is authorized to make war on the most secret of all U.S. government organizations. But Blackworks has some mighty big guns, and some even nastier tricks up their sleeves! What the Warriors don't realize, however is the result of this epic, worldwide battle might just unleash the greatest enemy they will ever know!
name: Black Works

description: The return of Mog threatens to change everything for the Forever Family. But not everyone will survive this reunion.
name: Mog

description:
This special edition marks the end of the relaunched Valiant Heroes universe.

Mog, the head of the Forever Family, has returned from sixty years of suspended animation in a glacier. His goal is to seize control of the Forever Family, and together with Blackworks forces, to take over the world. To stop this mad plan, his children must unite one final time, as well as enlist the aid of their mother. The result of this struggle will determine the fate of the world.
name: The Immortal Enemy

description: Homicron asks Starlock to assist the international organization CLASH with the disposal of atomic, bacteriological and chemical weapons stored in a space stationt, which finds itself attacked by the robotic army of the power-mad scientist known as Astaroth. Meanwhile, on Earth, Tanka enlists Futura's help, and attempts to rescue Jaleb from his comatose state, for he knows the telepath holds the key to their ultimate victory against an as yet unseen enemy.
name: Like an Angel, Feral-Eyed...

description:
"In the Inwards of the Night..."

In the orbiting space station, Homicron, Starlock and Futura join the forces of Clash to do battle with Astaroth who plots to blackmail Earth with the deadly weapons stored in its cargo. In Paris, Tanka shares his knowledge of events to come with the comatose JALEB. However, all is not what it seems, as a new villain is revealed, one who was secretly pulling manipulating Astaroth all along: the deadly Tarantula.
name: In the Shadows of the Night...

description:
"Caresses such as Snakes Give"

The TARANTULA plans to crash the Clash's space station on Earth with its deadly cargo, virtually ending all life on the planet. To insure her victory, she uses her deadliest pawn: Jaydee, an unstoppable, shapeshifting, killing organism, whom she unleashes on the Strangers. While on Earth, Tanka and Jaleb draw plans, in space a deadly countdown has begun. Finally, the mastermind behind the doomsday scheme is revealed: the Necromancer.
name: Caresses such as Snakes Give

description:
"The Livid Daylights"

From his Moonbase, the dying NECROMANCER schemes to turn Earth into his funeral pyre. But his passing would not be complete without the humiliation of his arch-enemies, the super-group known as HEXAGON. As the STRANGERS mount a last, desperate attempt on the Moonbase to stop the NECROMACER's suicidal plan, the villain turns HEXAGON against them -- but not all heroes will escape alive from the deadly confrontation.
name: The Livid Daylights

description:
"Icy till the Evening"

The NECROMANCER's threat to Earth is not over -- the villain has now taken refuge in his ultimate citadel: a station in orbit around the Sun, from which he plans to cause our star to go nova, using STARLOCK's precious starseed. The STRANGERS follow, and the final battle against the arch-villain takes place against the background of the Sun's murderous rays -- but can it be that it was all in vain?
name: Icy till the Evening
